on that. But there you can just go back to base R things that work just fine, and hopefully soon

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:35.800
that will also get figured out. And the final question, what was the process, what was your

00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:43.119
original data format? I mean, how do you go from paper record into vectors? Yeah, so it's fun

00:19:43.119 --> 00:19:53.040
thinking about the questions of big data, because I have to create all of my own data. And it's also

00:19:53.040 --> 00:19:57.839
funny to think about it in terms of reproducible data. Oh, don't change the data. And it's like,

00:19:57.839 --> 00:20:06.160
well, wait, I created, I can change it if I want to. But basically, I take these numbers, I take

